    stem: "A 35-year-old man with a known peanut allergy accidentally ate a meal containing peanut oil at a restaurant 20 minutes ago. He received his own adrenaline autoinjector (EpiPen 0.3 mg) at the scene with initial improvement but now redevelops hypotension (BP 75/40 mmHg), wheeze, and urticaria in the emergency department. He has received 1 L of IV normal saline. What is the most appropriate next step?",
