    stem: "A 45-year-old man with depression presents to the ED 2 hours after ingesting approximately 25 tablets of paracetamol 500 mg with alcohol. He is alert (GCS 15) and feels mildly nauseated. His initial paracetamol level is 450 mg/L at 2 hours post-ingestion. His LFTs and INR are normal. What is the most appropriate management?",
