    explanation: `Irukandji syndrome is a painful, potentially lethal condition caused by certain jellyfish from the Cubozoa class (box jellyfish) species. This species has a small body (the size of a coin) and usually four tentacles. The sting is usually mild and often goes unnoticed by the victim; however, after 20-30 minutes of the sting, a surge of catecholamine results in tachycardia, hypertension, agitation, and generalized severe pain and cramps especially in the abdomen and back. Hypotension, pulmonary edema, and potentially life-threatening cardiac complications can follow. Victims should be transferred to the hospital for analgesia (oral and IV), investigation and treatment of cardiac effects (echocardiogram, troponin), and cardiac monitoring.`,
